PN,36210
SC,0010
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F362A1778217983
OL,3,CMurder accused told Ian Watkins 'have
OL,4,Ca good sleep' after stabbing, court
OL,5,Chears
OL,7,FDodsworth glanced at the item and put
OL,8,Fit in the pocket of his jogging
OL,9,Fbottoms, jurors heard.
OL,11,FFootage showed Watkins emerging
OL,12,Fbriefly from his cell with blood
OL,13,Fvisible on the neck of his T-shirt.
OL,15,FTwo workmen who were carrying out
OL,16,Fmaintenance work in the prison saw he
OL,17,Fwas holding his hand to his neck, and
OL,18,Fbleeding from a wound.
OL,1,Woz5~k4{$z%~s1z5jw=hw1        G10/15
OL,2,W,.!+.!/*%/*%,.!/*%/*%/"-$T,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BYorks News CReg TV FThis Day
FL,363,360,260,120,000,100
PN,36211
SC,0011
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F362A1778217983
OL,3,CMurder accused told Ian Watkins 'have
OL,4,Ca good sleep' after stabbing, court
OL,5,Chears
OL,7,FThey signalled for help and three
OL,8,Fprison officers ran towards Watkins'
OL,9,Fcell, where he was bleeding from his
OL,10,Finjuries.
OL,12,FOne officer used his radio to summon
OL,13,Furgent help while pressing a towel
OL,14,Fagainst a "particularly large wound"
OL,15,Fto the side of Watkins' neck.
OL,17,FMr Storey said he asked who had done
OL,18,Fthis, and Watkins "said something to
OL,19,Fthe effect of 'that little black
OL,20,Ffella'".
OL,26,@vD@KOUvD@dO]zD@SOU|D@GO]
OL,1,Woz5~k4{$z%~s1z5jw=hw1        G11/15
OL,2,W,.!+.!/*%/*%,.!/*%/*%/"-$T,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BYorks News CReg TV FThis Day
FL,363,360,260,120,000,100
PN,36212
SC,0012
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F362A1778217983
OL,3,CMurder accused told Ian Watkins 'have
OL,4,Ca good sleep' after stabbing, court
OL,5,Chears
OL,7,FWatkins, from Merthyr Tydfil in Wales,
OL,8,Fcollapsed onto his bed and lost
OL,9,Fconsciousness.
OL,11,FParamedics were unable to resuscitate
OL,12,Fhim and he was declared dead just
OL,13,Fbefore 10.15am.
OL,15,FBefore all prisoners were locked in
OL,16,Ftheir cells, Dodsworth was seen going
OL,17,Finto an alcove with some bins.
OL,19,FA homemade knife with blood on it was
OL,20,Ffound at the bottom of one of the bins
OL,21,Fby prison officers.
OL,1,Woz5~k4{$z%~s1z5jw=hw1        G12/15
OL,2,W,.!+.!/*%/*%,.!/*%/*%/"-$T,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BYorks News CReg TV FThis Day
FL,363,360,260,120,000,100
PN,36213
SC,0013
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F362A1778217983
OL,3,CMurder accused told Ian Watkins 'have
OL,4,Ca good sleep' after stabbing, court
OL,5,Chears
OL,7,FWhen Gedel was interviewed by police
OL,8,Fhe told officers that there was no
OL,9,Fsegregation between sex offenders and
OL,10,Fother prisoners in HMP Wakefield and
OL,11,Fhe "thought it was disgusting having
OL,12,Fto share wings with offenders like
OL,13,Fthat," Mr Storey said.
OL,15,FWhen asked who had caused the injuries
OL,16,Fto Watkins, Gedel replied, "God (who)
OL,17,Fdoes everything."
OL,19,FDodsworth told police he had not been
OL,20,Finvolved in the incident and tried to
OL,21,Fgive the knife back to Gedel.
OL,26,@sD@DOUuD@FO]xD@\OUyD@QO]
OL,1,Woz5~k4{$z%~s1z5jw=hw1        G13/15
OL,2,W,.!+.!/*%/*%,.!/*%/*%/"-$T,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BYorks News CReg TV FThis Day
FL,363,360,260,120,000,100
PN,36214
SC,0014
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F362A1778217983
OL,3,CMurder accused told Ian Watkins 'have
OL,4,Ca good sleep' after stabbing, court
OL,5,Chears
OL,7,FHe said he put the blade in the bin
OL,8,F"in panic" after seeing Watkins
OL,9,Fstanding at his door with a big gash
OL,10,Fon his neck.
OL,12,FMr Storey said: "He (said he) knew
OL,13,Fthat Watkins was high profile, and
OL,14,Fthat he was serving a sentence for
OL,15,Fsexual offences, but other than that
OL,16,Fdid not know much about him.
OL,18,F"He said that sometimes Watkins would
OL,19,Fget beaten up, and sometimes he
OL,20,Fwouldn't ` Wakefield was a high-risk
OL,21,Fprison."
OL,26,@pD@AOUpD@JO]tD@QOUzD@AOU}D@HO]
OL,1,Woz5~k4{$z%~s1z5jw=hw1        G14/15
